Facundus (viii. 4) relates that Theodore was the author of several works directed against Apollinarianism: “agebat enim Theodorus frequenter tam libris quam sermonibus in populum contra synusiastas siue (ut ab auctoris sui nomine sunt uocati) Apollinaristas.” The books on the Incarnation would doubtless fall under this description, and a treatise expressly directed against Apollinarius is cited by Facundus further on (x. 1)= see this fragment infla, p. 321.
